A Python script that outputs detailed information about a Steam library to
a Google spreadsheet.

Setup:
  * install dependencies with `pip install -r requirements.txt`
  * install SteamCMD as per fourth step of [1] and cache your credentials
    by logging in once manually
  * setup OAuth2 for Google as per [2]
  * create `config.json` with the following fields:

  Field             | What it is        | Where to find it
  ------------------+-------------------+-------------------------------------
  api_key           | Steam API key     | [3]
  json_keyfile_path | OAuth2 file       | [2]
  spreadsheet_key   | Google Sheets key | URL of spreadsheet
  steam_login       | Your login nick   | Top-right part of Steam store
  steamid           | steamID64         | [4]

All files must be on the same folder as the script, but it can be executed
from anywhere with

    $ python /path/to/manager.py

[1] https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/SteamCMD#Manually
[2] http://gspread.readthedocs.org/en/latest/oauth2.html
[3] http://steamcommunity.com/dev/apikey
[4] https://steamdb.info/calculator/
